        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 9:44AM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 944 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a slow-moving thunderstorm
over DePue, or near Hennepin. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Minor flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Slowing or redirecting of traffic due to ponding or flowing
water. Closure of waterfront access due to flooding.

Locations impacted include...
Princeton, Hennepin, Spring Valley, DePue, Ladd, Dalzell, Bureau
Junction, Cherry, Seatonville, Hollowayville, Coal Hollow, Ottville,
and Bureau  County Fairgrounds.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 80 in Illinois between mile markers 55 and 72.
Interstate 180 between mile markers 6 and 13.

Rainfall amounts of 1 to 2 inches have fallen and an additional 1
to 2 inches of rain are possible.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring and may lead to localized flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways. Stay away from
flooded areas. Report any flooding to local law enforcement.

If the heavy rain continues, a flash flood warning may be needed.</instruction>
